  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Andhra Bank has typically required customers to visit a branch to complete the initial registration for internet banking. However, many banks have been moving towards more digital processes, which may allow for some aspects of internet banking registration to be completed online.\n\nTo get the most accurate and current information, it\u2019s best to:\n\n1. **Visit the official Andhra Bank website:** Check if they have updated their process for internet banking registration.\n2. **Contact customer service:** You can call or email their customer service for the latest information regarding internet banking application processes.\n3. **Mobile banking app:** If you have the Andhra Bank mobile banking app, check if it offers options for internet banking registration.\n\nPlease verify with the bank directly, as policies and procedures may change.",
